```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.tiktokcommentsection">

    <!-- 
        The application name identifies the TikTok comment section marketing tool.
        This tool aims to streamline social media management by automating the interaction processes within TikTok.
    -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.DayNight.DarkActionBar">
        
        <!-- MainActivity serves as the entry point of the application. 
             This is where users interact with the app to configure their automation preferences. -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            AutomationService works in the background to execute automation tasks.
            This service continuously runs to ensure the tools provided by MadHub operate 24/7 without user intervention. 
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" />

    </application>

    <!-- 
        Permissions are essential for enabling the app to perform necessary functions. 
        Each permission addresses specific challenges faced by users in social media marketing.
    -->

    <!-- 
        This permission allows the app to access the internet, solving the problem of connecting to TikTok API 
        for automated interactions and updates. It ensures data can be sent and received reliably.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />

    <!-- 
        Access to external storage is required for saving user configurations and logs.
        This addresses the challenge of persistent data management, allowing users to maintain their settings 
        even after closing the app.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <!-- 
        Wake lock permission is crucial for keeping the device awake during crucial automation tasks.
        This solves the limitation of Android's battery management that might interrupt background processes essential 
        for consistent operation in social media marketing.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WAKE_LOCK" />

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **Application Name and Package**: Clearly defines the purpose of the app and its unique identity.
- **MainActivity**: The initial user interface where settings can be configured, addressing the need for user engagement in automation.
- **AutomationService**: Ensures continuous operation, tackling the challenge of needing persistent social media management.
- **Permissions**: 
  - **Internet Access**: Enables necessary connectivity, vital for any online interaction.
  - **Storage Access**: Facilitates persistent data retention, overcoming the hurdles of application closures.
  - **Wake Lock**: Prevents disruptions during crucial tasks, ensuring reliability in automation. 

This configuration aligns with MadHub's capability to provide a comprehensive social media management tool while adhering to best practices and compliance standards.
